  "rationale": "The page follows the brief's arc \u2014 reveal, what shipped, who believes it, the ask \u2014 as four sections plus the appended footer chrome. The hero adopts the Swiss split-left posture (adapted from the project photo-overlay seed): the claim lives in a left-flush serif display stack with a single filled-orange primary and an outline secondary, while the Breeze platform graphic counterweights the right column, so no type touches the photo and the sanctioned text-on-media hero isn't needed. 'What shipped' renders the four agents as one parallel four-up cards run with numeral eyebrows and no decorative icons, honoring the feature-trio grammar extended to four peers. Belief transfer splits into a light stat band (12,000+ / 135+ / 4, serif stat numerals) and a single verbatim quote split (text left, figure right). The close reuses the deep-teal closing-cta-dark band \u2014 the only mid-run dark surface, at the end, per never-dark-mid-page \u2014 with one primary and a quiet demo action. Accent orange stays on controls and the mark only; all headings are sentence case ending in periods; every section declares an explicit anchor with a real counterweight slot. No off-grid treatments were used: clean-SaaS trust comes from disciplined alignment."
